{
  "text": "Protoplasts (0.6 x 10 6 per sample) were transfected with plasmid DNA (10 tig of p35SISceI+ or p35SISceI-and 0.5 ng pAFlOONl or 0.5 fig pAF100C4) . Total DNA was isolated from the protoplasts 8 hours after transfection, as previously described (27) . After restriction digestion with EcoO109I and gel electrophoresis, Southern blotting was performed, as described [CITATION_1] , using the hybridization membrane 'Hybond N' (DuPont, Boston, USA). The 0.75 kb fragment, obtained from pGUS 23 by cleavage with Acc65I and MscI (see 26), was labeled with a-32 P-ATP using the random primed labeling kit of Boehringer (Mannheim, FRG) and was used as hybridization probe.",
